Laparoscopic cholecystectomy.
 This article describes the first 50 laparoscopic cholecystectomies emphasizing the two-handed technique that is currently used at Marietta Surgical Center, Marietta, Georgia.
 This procedure has become primarily an outpatient procedure with resumption of normal activities in 7 days (including athletics).
 Two patients in this series had complications.
 One patients was converted to an open procedure because of a common duct injury.
 The other patient developed a biloma 2 weeks following surgery and recovered uneventfully following paracentesis on an outpatient basis.
